-- Lagarde Says Pension Reform Must Be Rapid; No Threat to Triple-A Rating
-- David Whitehouse
-- 2010-06-25T06:25:49Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-25/lagarde-says-pension-reform-must-be-rapid-no-threat-to-triple-a-rating.html

          
          
             France’s public finances mean that
reform of the country’s pension system must be rapid, Finance
Minister Christine Lagarde said.  
 There’s no reason to think that the country’s triple A
credit rating is under threat, she said. She’s speaking on
France Inter radio station.  
          
          


  


        